#Text=Tragedy, comedy, burlesque, poetry, music, prose, and  pictures" are supplied in lavish profusion, until the reader is almost inclined to think that he has too much for his money.

column1: #Text=Not that any page is dull reading.
#Text=The difficulty is on the other side, and the danger lies in the direction of excessive laughter, or of being surfeited with good things.
#Text=There is something to suit every age in a household, and they must be a dull lot who are not all set laughing.

#Text=Tom Hood— who inherits so much of his fathers genius — acts as editor, and that fact is a sufficient guarantee of the merit of "Five Alls ;" but there is also a number of well-known writers, who have philosophy, wit, wisdom, entertainment, and fun to offer.
#Text=The total result is 100 pages of the most acceptable kind ever offered for a shilling. * "Warnes Christmas Annual: Five Alls."
